        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">1, Harewood Place, | Hanover Square. W.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>May 12. 1875.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I beg you to let me thus introduce to you M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Burgers, the President of the Trans-Vaal Republic—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> He is devoted to Natural Science, anxious to know you, and ready to assist you in any investigations that you may wish to be made in his country—</p>
<p>Sincerely your’s | James Paget <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Cha<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>. Darwin Esq.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_734.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas François Burgers</ref> was president of the Transvaal Republic from 1871 to 1877. The Transvaal Republic was in the north-eastern part of southern Africa, bounded by the Vaal river in the south and the Limpopo river in the north.</note>
        </div>        
            
